			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Show me the way.<a name="22211"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 18 04 3:50 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Heya Haard,
<br />

<br />
Nice to see you here...
<br />

<br />
Here are my thoughts (probably obvious) and they are certainly up for debate:
<br />

<br />
Key Bard stats are STA/Raw HP, CHA, and DEX.  
<br />

<br />
Stamina determines the amount of HP you have and is generally a difficult stat to raise.  This is because its generally the most sought after stat by most players classes, particularly at the end of the game and there is high competition for the items.  Its all about surviving that nasty AE or the one round tag from a PoP boss.  
<br />

<br />
Charisma is a key stat in your lulling and charming ability.  Charisma is checked when you have a failure to lull.  It determines the mobs response once a failure occurs.  So you can fail and if your Charisma is high enough the mob doesn't agro.  Critical in your role as a puller.  It also plays a role in how long our charms last but I don't think I can speak intelligently on this, and hasn't been a large concern for me.  
<br />

<br />
Dexterity effects the number of missed notes that occur when you are twisting.  You just don't want your groove thrown off by missing notes.
<br />

<br />
Having said all that, you should balance your stats against this.  I would try and raise your stamina, which at the moment is just over the lowest end of acceptability.  In addition, as a rule I don't equip items, if I can help it, that don't contribute Raw HP.  You could definitely stand to take a hit in the CHA department. Grab yourself a CHA buff from a shammy or chanter that will make up for any lacking when you are participating in the specific act of pulling.
<br />

<br />
Specific examples are:
<br />
Finger: 2 x <a target="_new" href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4243">Velium Fire Wedding Ring</a>
<br />
Wrist: bag the Sarnak Bracer for pulling and get something like <a target="_new" href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=8969">Bracelet of Fortitude</a>, <a target="_new" href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=6309">Silver Chitin Wristband</a>, 
<br />
Arms: Sell the SS arms and get <a target="_new" href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=3932">Crystal Chitin Armplates</a>
<br />
Feet: Bag and keep the SS boots and get <a target="_new" href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=23565">Steelslave Bladed Boots</a>
<br />
Ear: Do the quest for an <a target="_new" href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=12456">Earring of the Solstice</a>
<br />

<br />
hope this helps
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
