				<td colspan="2"><span>Sharoo,
<br />

<br />
Perhaps you are right that we aren't tanks.  What we are is a multitude of things.  STA/HP is the key to surviving so many encounters.  It is key in pulling in LDoN and a great many other encounters, as you will absolutely get one rounded constantly.  As a rule if there aren't 2 or 3 mobs in camp in an LDoN group, the people I group with start calling me names.  This means I get tagged a lot as I lock them down.  
<br />

<br />
It's key when you, along with everyone else in your group/raid eat an AoE from a mob or you inadvertently take rampage damage.
<br />

<br />
I suspect that if you asked any 65 bard what he would like more of in the stat department, their answer would be HPs.
<br />

<br />
I would love for my mana pool to be larger than it is, but it takes an extreme backseat to my HPs.
<br />

<br />
Of course, just my opinion...I have been known to be wrong.  Can't remember when though.  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" /></span></td>
